balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}. Requirements: - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.

params.amount: Amount of tokens to be burned
params.owner: Owner of the tokens being burned
params.tokenId: ID of the token to be burned

params.showId: The unique identifier of the show.
params.ticketId: The unique identifier of the ticket.

returns.price: The price paid for the ticket.
returns.tierIndex: The index of the ticket tier.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

params.paymentToken: Address of the currency the ticket is priced in
params.tierIndex: Index of the ticket tier from which to purchase tickets

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.newDefaultURI: The new default URI for tickets.

params.newURI: New URI to set for the token
params.showId: ID of the show for which to set the URI
params.tokenId: Token ID for which to set the URI

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

MAX_TICKETS_PER_WALLET().notice: Maximum number of tickets that a single wallet can purchase for a given show.

boxOfficeInstance().notice: Reference to the Box Office contract interface to interact with ticket-related functionalities.

burnTokens(uint256,uint256,address).notice: Burns a specific amount of tokens, removing them from circulation

getTicketPricePaidAndTierIndex(bytes32,u.notice: Retrieves the price paid for a specific ticket and its tier index.

purchaseTickets(bytes32,uint256,uint256,.notice: Purchase multiple tickets for a specific show from a specific tier

setDefaultURIForShow(bytes32,string).notice: Sets the default URI for tickets related to a specific show.

setTokenURI(bytes32,uint256,string).notice: Sets the URI for a given token ID

showInstance().notice: Reference to the Show contract interface to interact with show-related functionalities.

showVaultInstance().notice: Reference to the ShowVault contract interface to interact with ticket-related functionalities.
